===Etymology===
From {{etyl|enm}} {{term|regretten|regretten||lang=enm}}, from {{etyl|fro}} {{term|regreter||to lament}}, from ''[[re-]]'' ''(intensive prefix)'' + {{term||greter|lang=fro}} "to weep", of {{etyl|gem}} origin, from {{etyl|frk}} *{{term||grêtan||lang=frk}} "to weep, mourn, lament", from {{proto|Germanic|grētanan|to weep|lang=}} and {{etyl|frk|-}} *{{term||grêotan||lang=frk}} "to cry, weep", from {{proto|Germanic|griutanan|to weep, cry|lang=en}}, from {{proto|Indo-European|ghrew-|to weep, be sad|lang=en}}. Cognate with {{etyl|gmh|-}} {{term|grazan|grāzan||lang=goh}} "to cry", {{etyl|ang|-}} {{term|grætan|grǣtan|to weep, greet|sc=Latinx|lang=ang}}, {{etyl|ang|-}} ''[[greotan|grēotan]]'' "to weep, lament", {{etyl|non|-}} {{term|gráta||to weep, groan|lang=non}}, {{etyl|got|-}} {{term|𐌲𐍂𐌴𐍄𐌰𐌽||to weep|tr=gretan|lang=got|sc=Goth}}. More at [[greet]].

===Pronunciation===
* {{a|US}} {{IPA|/ɹiˈɡɹɛt/|/ɹəˈɡɹɛt/}}
* {{audio|en-us-regret.ogg|Audio (US)}}
* {{rhymes|ɛt}}

===Verb===
{{en-verb|regrett|ing}}

# To [[feel]] [[sorry]] about (a thing that has happened), [[afterthink]]: to [[wish]] that a thing had [[not]] [[happen]]ed, that something else had happened instead.
#: ''He '''regretted''' his words.''
# {{context|more generally}} To feel sorry about (any thing).
#: ''I '''regret''' that I have to do this, but I don't have a choice.''

====Usage notes====
* This is a [[catenative]] verb that takes the [[gerund]] (the {{term|-ing}} form), except in set phrases with [[tell]], [[say]], and [[inform]], where the '''to infinitive''' is used. See [[Appendix:English catenative verbs]]

